  "texts": [
    "Multiple studies have successfully applied LoRA to specific test scenarios, such as generating tests for complex C++ projects [17], creating tests capturing exceptional behavior [164], and generating tests for game engine APIs [107].",
    "Research has even explored integrating multiple PEFT techniques (such as prompt tuning and LoRA) into a multi-task learning framework to further enhance fine-tuning efficiency and cross-domain generalization capabilities [23].",
    "Although specialized research indicates a slight performance trade-off compared to FFT, PEFT achieves comparable results at a fraction of the cost, making it a highly practical alternative for most applications [130].",
    "Domain Adaptation.",
    "This represents a domain-specific fine-tuning strategy designed to equip the model with project-specific or framework-specific idiomatic knowledge."
